caption: It's just average sandwiches

Horrible, terrible, disrespectful place. Yesterday March 11, 2021 around 9:45pm Me and my two kids and my friend and his son went to jimmy johns in downtown Tampa. I ordered sandwiches worth $42. The cashier was such a good person. A black lady was preparing our sandwiches she was to nervous and angry. After she finished preparing our sandwiches she thrown our sandwiches in a dirty box and through napkins and told to come grab my food in a very disrespectful way. I asked her if she can put my sandwiches in a bag she started yelling at me. I asked for the manager she said that she is the manager. She kept talking while I was putting my sandwiches in the bags and making fun on me and kept disrespect me in front of my kids. I kept silent and left. This not acceptable at all. I will do my best to shut down this place while they hiring such a horrible employees like her.

I had a terrible experience at this location. I was there on a Monday night around 9:30 and the lady there treated me with a lot of disrespect. It was my first time at Jimmy Johns and when I said thank you to her after eating, she told me to go back and pick up my stuff on the table and throw it away in a very disrespectful manner. My friend and I said sorry and went back and picked it up but I was treated very poorly by her and her friend who was sitting there talking to her. It was our first time there, and even though I explained that to her, she was still very rude. I’m not her buddy, I’m a customer and deserve respect. Don’t go here if you don’t want to leave in a very low state of mind.

Good customer service and indoor/outdoor dining. Being that I only had an 8" Tuna Sub, scant comment to much more other than to say the Tuna was Good. If a restaurant cant make good Tuna at least they may need to Reevaluate some things

I want to inform everyone do not go to Jimmy Johns if you are hungry. I been receiving only half the sub with the protein protion and Icalled and asked why and they told me the meat portion is already weighed out. So basically everyone is getting ripped off almost $9 for 8inch sub with half the meat.i will say they have fresh food but thats it.
Fast, clean, very hospitable, covid conscious. Food is fresh and taste very good. Customer service is excellent.

I live this job working here is fun has its ups and downs like and other job,be we are freaky fast,and we have free smells come by and enjoy a fresh freaky fast sub u won't regret it ( were only as good as our last sandwich) which did I mention is fresh and freaky fast lol
Healthy and delicious sandwich , fast service and great people

Strong Miscommunication! This location notified me that I am out of their range and there is nothing they can do. I am 1.1 miles from this location. I am 1.1 miles from the other location. Which Jimmy Johns can I get a delivery from? This one can't go across the water and the people at the other one said they can do it this time but not to get used to it. I just want a delicious gargantuan that I don't have to leave the house for. This is a very Karen move but im giving both locations 1 star until we find out who is delivering to West Arch Street. Gave this one 2 because the person who answered the phone actually tried to help
Great place
Quick spot to grab a bite. Great for on-the-go groups who want to travel and eat, but not wait long for a snack/meal.

They provided exceptional service today! We put a large (25 people) order 20 minutes before we had a meeting. Normally we order days ahead but it totally slipped our minds today. From the time we placed the order, until the time it got delivered it was 37 minutes... Talk about freaky fast. The accuracy was 100% also. Nothing from the order was missing and the taste remained just as tasty as a single sandwich. Will definitely order from them again!

Ordered at 12:41, I called at 1:10, guy answers the phone, says please hold, then hangs up on me. I call back 1:12, a lady answers says they're super busy. She wasnt rude, but where is the apology that a sandwich couldn't be made in that time frame? No apology. I requested to just refund my money. Hopefully they can refund me in a timely matter.
Food is always great but the employees are usually nit listening or rolling their eyes! :(

Came in with my family looking to get Jimmy johns and was greeted by whom identified himself as the manager of Jimmy Johns “Andre _______” at 12:03. I was absolutely horrified by the way he spoke to my wife as she was uncertain in her order. I am unsure as to why the manager displayed himself in such an unprofessional way but through trying to contact customer service on this location after my experience I was unsuccessful. Unluckily, I have to leave this review so that any remedial action towards this employee can be made and the service can be improved.

Terrible customer service. I couldn’t even order anything and had to leave cause they were so terrible. I’ve never heard of a jimmy Johns, or any sandwich place in general, that won’t let you customize a meal. All my 4yr old son wanted was a ham and cheese sandwich with salami and they told me that was in no way possible. No matter how many different ways I tried asking! Seriously?! He tried to tell me I could only order one type of sandwich for my son and I had no other options. Ridiculous. They have salami and they have ham, he wouldn’t even let me order a whole sandwich with that. Terrible customer service.
Freaky fast!
Tampa
Standard Jimmy John's. Staff was friendly. Restaurant was clean.
My order is always right, the staff is super friendly and the veggies are fresh. Great place to stop in for a quick and easy lunch!
Great Sub Shop
What can I say great sandwiches real quick..lol
It's a reason they can deliver in 5 minutes, no flavor. Why is the 🍞🥖 so hard?
As advertised they were freaky fast and my sandwich was built perfectly.
Delivery is super fast and sandwiches always made to what I ordered. Delivery people are very friendly.
Awesome cold subs freaky fast and clean bathrooms!!!!

So I was in town checking out the scene... next day needing some food, never had been to a Jimmy John's before (first time I ever saw one was in Philly)... so I got the tuna and with the Alfalfa... wow, I was just so happy... never quite felt the same whenever I've ordered it again at other locations in other parts of the country.
Always the perfect sandwich... And FAST too.

I always come here and the staff is always busy, in a good way. Only giving it 4 stars because when you come in around lunch time there's a heavy smell, I don't know what it is but it is overwhelming. Not in a good way.
It's freaky fast!🌴✌️😎🌴
no meat on sandwich(one skice of roast beef, never again.
Friendly staff
Love it.
Quick and filling

They deliver super quick and the delivery people are always extremely nice. Sandwiches are pretty basic but yummy. Sometimes they forget an ingredient here or there. Nothing life ruining, probably because they are moving so fast.
A decent place with good food and kind people. Nothing spectacular, but worth a stop.
It tastes good but kind of small
The food was good.
Excellent Service. Bartender was a sweetheart.

Generally very good restaurants. They can be over busy at certain times of the day.  My favorite is the "unwich" which is the sub contents wrapped in lettuce.  I don't visit them very frequently but find it is a nice change-of-pace though a little pricier than Subway or Quiznos. It's on price par with Jersey Mike's which I think was also overpriced.
Always delicious
My order was fast, accurate and correct.  Even better, my delivery person Hunter was so upbeat, pleasant and friendly.  Thanks again Jimmy Johns!!
Horrible service! They can’t seem to deliver my food on time!
Some of the best sandwiches!
Fast service and good food.
Freaky fast is right. I ordered my sandwich and had in with 15 minutes. I’ve never had a problem with these guys or any of the other locations.

Ordered the sandwich and was hungry since I was forced to skip breakfast. Was preparing to wait another hour to eat, as it was delivery. Was startled to see it here in less than 10 minutes. Kudos to the delivery guy! Thanks, I was starving and you were fast!
First time to a Jimmy John's. I believe the hype.
The fastest food delivery times on this planet.
Best subs
Can't go wrong with the beach club, even as an 'unwich' otherwise known as a lettuce wrap, if you're avoiding bread. If not, their bread is very good.

I work in a building in downtown. My coworkers order from here all the time. Sometimes, they're really freaky fast, sometimes they take almost an hour. Anyway, I tried them and they soaked my sandwich with Mayo when I didn't ask for any and don't like it, otherwise I would've eaten it cause I was starving. So I called and they said they would deliver a new one. Sure enough the new one was no better, missing ingredients. I get the whole freaky fast slogan but if you're NOT gonna get my order right then maybe you should just take your time. JS I ate the sandwich ONLY because I was starving but after waiting so long to eat, it kinda sucked having to eat something I wasn't really enjoying. ((Thumbs down))
Cheap Quick Not bad
Good subs... and Cookies
Always friendly and quick, even at correcting your order (all too common at this location 🤷🏼‍♂️)...
Good value, great folks
It's just bad, everything is very low quality, just do yourself a favor and order Jersey Mikes. You only eat here if you hate yourself.
I feel like they need to have a hot sandwich here they're old cold
Always an excellent customer service and fast delivery of fresh good quality sandwiches.
Fast, fresh, easy online ordering and speedy delivery  at great prices. What more could you want!
I love Vegi sandwich

Sometimes late - some delivery personnel is great and some are rude.  I work in a large building and I have had my food left on a table in a main lobby corridor.  I have had them call me from the main lobby of our building where security sits stating they were in the lobby when my instructions specifically state 23rd floor.  My co-worker has had her food delivered missing items.  I have each time made the store aware of the issues and they never even give an apology.  I wish I was not sometimes subjected to order here but when I'm crunched at work they are the only people who deliver in the area.  Please step up your attention to detail and customer service or else I will just start ordering someplace else PERIOD.

I ordered extra toppings, and a delayed delivery. They delivered the sandwich at the wrong time, couldn't find the place (one block away from the store) and I had to go outside. Additionally to that, instead of extra toppings they gave me so little of everything that you would need to hire a search and rescue crew to find out what I ordered. Then I tough that I could forget about the horrible sandwich and enjoy my pickle, after all how could they screw up a pickel. Wrong. I've had beef jerky less chewy than that.
Don't go
Just like the commercial quick and good

I love Jimmy John's but this location leaves a lot to be desired. During my visit there were at least two enraged customers at any one time. If it's your first time visiting a Jimmy John's, go elsewhere. Food is good quality, fast and affordable, but the staff at this location seem a little lost in life.
Clean location, fast service. The staff seemed to be having a swearing competition. While eating my lunch today I think I heard 20-25 F bombs.
Good and fast.
Lightning Fast Delivery.
Super fast and good sandwiches
Great subs

Just because their closing in an hour and a half is not a reason to sell a crappy sandwich. The bread & most ingredients were stale. I had to put extra mayonaise to soften and add flavor to my sandwich. I travel for work and frequently eat at different JJ's across the country, on average 20-30 times a year. I have never rated JJ's in the past as I have never had much to complain about. This location however, has left a sour taste in my mouth. I will not be coming back here again, even though im in Tampa for 10 more days of work. Also, staff was not very intuitive. Definitely not customer oriented. Don't really want to throw them under the bus as they are probably minimum wage employees and need their job. Perhaps the owner can help them to be more professional.
1 piece of turkey paid 11 bucks for a piece of bread
Good food and quality. Love the people.

Normally- I LOVE Jimmy johns. However this location specifically, service is terrible. They get busy due to games and conferences in the downtown Tampa area and frankly, they simply cannot handle having more than a few orders going at once. Slow service. Slow delivery. Rude staff. And for heavens sake good luck calling and talking to someone on the phone.
Fast and nice.
Good sandwiches. Better than Subway
First time coming to the Jimmy John's in downtown tampa and I love the service and the quality of the sandwiches and the subs.
Freakishly fast, great staff, very friendly.
Driver just left my order sitting at the entrance to my work. No call that it was there. And the order wasn't complete.

DELIVERY DRIVER GOT MAD BECAUSE HE SHOWED UP AN HOUR LATE AND I DIDN'T GIVE HIM A TIP, OH AND THIS WAS WITH A CREDIT I HAD FROM THE STORE FROM THE LAST TIME I ORDERED BECAUSE IT TOOK AN HOUR AND A HALF TO GET TO ME. I WORK DOWNTOWN, THEY OPERATE DOWNTOWN.  DRIVER THEN USES MY CELL PHONE NUMBER, WHICH HE GOT FROM MY ORDER AND CALLED ME PRIVATELY AND CUSSED ME OUT. COMPLETELY UNPROFESSIONAL AND HAVE TALKED TO CORPORATE. DO NOT EAT HERE AND SUPPORT THESE PEOPLE.
Terrible service
They are as fast as they say they are. The food is always fresh, and the bike delivery is awesome. Everyone loves downtown Jimmy John's.
Unprofessional attire and not sanitary conditions. The guy who took my order was wearing basketball shorts and constantly grabbing himself. As if he needed an anti inch cream.

They are really super fast in delivering your food to you - So fast it really is freakish.  So if you want a quick lunch and do not want to leave your desk this really is your best delivery option in downtown Tampa.  Quality of freshness of there breads, ingredients and meats is there but quantity can be hit or miss so your best bet is to go with the giant clubs as there regular subs are sparse on the main ingredients.  I mistakenly ordered the #3 "Totally Tuna" and the tuna was minimal it was almost the quantity of cheese spread and barley to the edge of the bread.  It left me wanting more.  My advise is stick with the giant club sandwiches.
It was ok. It works  when you don't want pizza. One of few places open late both during the week and on the  weekends. No parking  other than paid lot at this location.
It was delivered  fast and tasted good.  They took it direct  to the room which is very nice.  The pizza place makes you go down to the lobby.

Very rude delivery boys. One flew past me on his bike downtown at the corner of Tyler and Ashley, yelling at me and complaining I didn't give him enough room on the sidewalk. I was standing to the side of the walkway. He had plenty of room. Even if I did hear him sooner, its not like I would have had time to move because he was going so fast. I guess he wouldn't have had to go so fast if he was crossing when the pedestrian signal was on "walk" and not "stop."

Gets the job done, but that is about it.  Wont go back unless I have no other alternative.  I got a 8 inch tuna sub.  The spread of tuna was paper thin and didnt even cover all of the roll.  Bread was stale and tasteless.  I do NOT recommend.
Good food! Not enough places to sit inside.
Delivery made by bicycles. That's always Going to be faster downtown than a car I dig it. Awesome sandwiches in your hand in under 20 minutes, what more could you ask.

So much for their advertising of fast delivery service....Live less than a mile a way and will not deliver....will not cross the bridge to harbor island but I can meet them just on the other side, what a great idea..Guess I will be ordering from Pita Pit who is right next door to JJ  and delivers.
So fast! Hope he didn't run any red lights!
Very tasty sandwiches, reasonably priced, and they arrive SUPER FAST! :)
Food excellent, staff friendly, and restaurant clean. Prices are reasonable too. Would recommend.
Very, very fast service.  I ordered online and my sandwich arrived in less than 10 minutes.  AMAZING! My favorite sandwich is the Italian Night Club!

The sandwiches are extremely bland, and don't seem to have any real nutrition to speak of.  The people there are very nice and fast at serving you, but that isn't why i go to a restaurant during my busy lunch hour.  It's basically a subway without all the choices (meatball sub, etc).  -thanks
